                <head>No. 23.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rufus Magee</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-12-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 14, 1887</date>. (Received January 3,
                        1888.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 106.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your No. 55, under date of November 28 last.</p>
                <p>Since 1827 there have been no discriminating duties charged in Norwegian ports on
                    vessels arriving from ports of any country. The rates since that period on all
                    vessels, except as stated in my No. 101 as to small fishing vessels from the
                    White and Arctic Seas, has been uniform, no geographical distinction being
                    made.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rufus Magee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
